 "markdown", "html": "<p>since gazebojs will mostly be used as a bridge, its kind of a good idea to have sth like this</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-python\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">boost</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">shared_ptr</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">gazebo</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">msgs</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Response</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">response</span>\n          <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">gazebo</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">transport</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">request</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;heightmap_data&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>in it, we actually send requests alots through gazebojs and gazebow. </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2016-08-10T16:16:03.423295+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-08-10T16:16:03.423295+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 20}